Class WorldMenuBar

    • javafx.scene.Node

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    javafx.css.Styleable, javafx.event.EventTarget, javafx.scene.control.Skinnable

    public class WorldMenuBar
extends javafx.scene.control.MenuBar
    This class creates a menu bar that contains several buttons that can influence the antfarm simulation depicted via WorldPane.
    Version:
    4/17/2019
    Author:
    Elijah, Jongin, Justin, Christian

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      private class  WorldMenuBar.MenuHandler
      This class registers when any of the menu buttons have been clicked and does the appropriate action depending on which one was selected.

    • Constructor Detail

      • WorldMenuBar

        public WorldMenuBar(WorldPane worldPane)
        Creates a WorldMenubar object with 5 menus and 14 menu items and assigns each of them to an event listener. This WorldMenuBar will cause changes in the WorldPane class given as its parameter.
        Parameters:
        worldPane - The WorldPane object that this WorldMenuBar will affect.
